{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"wait-solar-haste","description":"## Why\n\nProvenance an auditor can't see isn't useful. The gate-code version+SHA stamp\n(stories 1-2) must be visible where attestations are inspected (epic\njira-reb-596).\n\n## What\n\n- Surface `manifest_rebar_version()` output in the `show` attestation rendering\n  (attestation data rides in the ticket state dict; render it in the show path in\n  `src/rebar/_reads.py` / `src/rebar/__init__.py` alongside the certified/verdict\n  block, HMAC still stripped).\n- Add the stamp to `verify_signature`'s return payload AND its typed contract:\n  the `VerifySignatureResultOut` model in `src/rebar/mcp_server.py` and the JSON\n  schema `src/rebar/schemas/verify_signature_result.schema.json` (new **nullable\n  string** field, e.g. `rebar_version`).\n- Pre-stamp manifests -> field is `None` / omitted; render nothing (no crash).\n\n## Scope\n\nRead/display surface + typed-contract extension only. Consumes story 1's parser.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `rebar show <id>` displays the gate-code version+SHA for a stamped\n      attestation.\n- [ ] `verify_signature` returns the stamp; `VerifySignatureResultOut` and\n      `verify_signature_result.schema.json` are extended with the nullable field.\n- [ ] A pre-stamp attestation shows/returns no stamp (field `None`) without error.\n- [ ] Tests cover `show` AND `verify_signature` for stamped and pre-stamp\n      attestations, including the schema/model validation of the new field.","id":"090f-4f7c-44ba-49ae","parent_id":"jira-reb-596","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Surface rebar-version stamp in show + verify_signature"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783123877215774001,"uuid":"cf7f00ad-f1e1-4b2f-9d89-b957df869d86"}